</style>

<div class="header">
  <div class="header-content">
    <div class="tag">Compiled by Gemini 3.1</div>
    <h1>Amgen (AMGN)<br/>Intrinsic Value</h1>
    <p class="subtitle">A transparent, two-stage discounted cash flow valuation of Amgen Inc. — using disclosed assumptions, and one final number.</p>
    <p class="date">Updated March 24, 2026</p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="container">
  {roundedIV !== null ? (
    <>
      <!-- ═══ THE VERDICT ═══ -->
      <div class="verdict-card">
        <div class="verdict-label">Estimated Intrinsic Value Per Share</div>
        <div class="verdict-price">${roundedIV.toFixed(2)}</div>
        <div class="verdict-vs">
          vs. market price of ${currentPrice !== null ? currentPrice.toFixed(2) : "N/A"}
          {marginOfSafety !== null ? `(${marginOfSafety}%)` : ""}
        </div>
        <div class="verdict-badge" style={`background: ${verdictColor}22; color: ${verdictColor}; border: 1px solid ${verdictColor}44;`}>
          {verdictText}
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- ═══ KEY METRICS ═══ -->
      <div class="stats-row">
        <div class="stat-card">
          <div class="stat-value">${(revenueHistory[revenueHistory.length - 1]?.value / 1000).toFixed(1)}B</div>
          <div class="stat-label">FY Revenue</div>
        </div>
        <div class="stat-card">
          <div class="stat-value">${(fcf2025 / 1000).toFixed(1)}B</div>
          <div class="stat-label">Free Cash Flow</div>
        </div>
        <div class="stat-card">
          <div class="stat-value">${epsHistory[epsHistory.length - 1]?.value.toFixed(2)}</div>
          <div class="stat-label">EPS (Diluted)</div>
        </div>
        <div class="stat-card">
          <div class="stat-value">{marginHistory[marginHistory.length - 1]?.operating}%</div>
          <div class="stat-label">Operating Margin</div>
        </div>
        <div class="stat-card">
          <div class="stat-value">${(netCash / 1000).toFixed(1)}B</div>
          <div class="stat-label">Net Cash</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </>
  ) : (
    <div class="verdict-card" style="margin-top: 60px;">
      <h2 style="margin: 0; border: none;">Data Unavailable</h2>
      <p>Could not fetch complete financial data for Amgen.</p>
    </div>
  )}

  <!-- ═══ METHODOLOGY ═══ -->
  <h2>Methodology: Two-Stage DCF</h2>
  <p>We use a <strong>two-stage discounted cash flow (DCF)</strong> model — the gold standard of intrinsic valuation. No multiples, no comparables, no vibes. Just future cash flows discounted to today.</p>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">1</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Start with actual Free Cash Flow</h4>
      <p>Amgen generated <strong>${fcf2025 !== null ? (fcf2025 / 1000).toFixed(2) : 'N/A'} billion</strong> in free cash flow recently. This is real cash the business produces after paying for everything, including R&D and capital expenditures.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">2</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Project FCF growth for 5 years (Phase 1)</h4>
      <p>We grow FCF at <strong>{(growthRatePhase1 * 100)}% per year</strong> for 5 years. This reflects Amgen's position as a mature biopharmaceutical company with an established product portfolio and pipeline.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">3</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Calculate terminal value (Phase 2)</h4>
      <p>After Year 5, we assume FCF grows at <strong>{(growthRateTerminal * 100)}% forever</strong> — roughly in line with inflation and long-term economic growth. We use the <strong>Gordon Growth Model</strong>.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">4</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Discount everything to present value</h4>
      <p>All future cash flows are discounted at <strong>{(discountRate * 100)}%</strong> — our required rate of return, based on a risk premium over the 10Y Treasury yield of {treasury10Y}%.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">5</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Add net cash, divide by shares</h4>
      <p>Enterprise Value + Net Cash (${netCash !== null ? (netCash / 1000).toFixed(1) : 'N/A'}B) = Equity Value. Divide by shares outstanding ({sharesOutstanding !== null ? sharesOutstanding.toFixed(0) : 'N/A'}M) for the per-share intrinsic value.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ THE THREE ASSUMPTIONS ═══ -->
  <h2>The Three Assumptions That Drive Everything</h2>
  <p>A DCF is only as good as its inputs. We're making exactly <strong>three</strong> judgment calls — everything else is math. Here's what we chose and why.</p>

  <div class="assumption-grid">
    <div class="assumption-card">
      <div class="label">FCF Growth Rate (Years 1-5)</div>
      <div class="value">{(growthRatePhase1 * 100)}%</div>
      <div class="rationale">
        Amgen is a mature biotech giant. While newer drugs (like Repatha and Evenity) show strong growth, older legacy drugs face biosimilar competition. A 5% growth rate represents steady mid-single-digit execution over the next 5 years.
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="assumption-card">
      <div class="label">Discount Rate (WACC)</div>
      <div class="value">{(discountRate * 100)}%</div>
      <div class="rationale">
        10Y Treasury: {treasury10Y}%. We use 8% as our required rate of return. Healthcare and pharmaceuticals generally have more defensive cash flows compared to cyclical tech, justifying a slightly lower discount rate than the standard 10% hurdle.
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="assumption-card">
      <div class="label">Terminal Growth Rate</div>
      <div class="value">{(growthRateTerminal * 100)}%</div>
      <div class="rationale">
        Long-term nominal GDP growth is ~3%. We use 2% for Amgen because patent cliffs eventually catch up to all pharma companies, and maintaining growth into perpetuity is structurally difficult without massive ongoing M&A.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  {projectedFCF.length > 0 && (
    <>
      <!-- ═══ FCF PROJECTIONS TABLE ═══ -->
      <h2>Projected Free Cash Flows</h2>
      <div class="table-wrap">
        <table>
          <thead>
            <tr>
